# ingredients
||peanut butter cups (snack & miniature sizes)
||chocolate kisses
||white chocolate (or candy melts)
||white non-pariels

# instructions
Melt the white chocolate (this will be the “glue” that holds each layer together) and put it in a squeeze bottle or ziptop bag with a tiny cutoff corner
Set up an assembly line -Tree trunk - upside down mini PB cup - white chocolate “glue” -1st layer - upside down snack size PB cup - drizzle white chocolate around the edges & sprinkle with non-pariels
